//Page 06 - Osteochondral Interface

Osteoarthrosis//


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 06 -Findings of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Osteoarthrosis' from the Finding dropdown
Then multiple selection Localizer is enabled

And 'Osteophytes' checkbox is enabled
And 'Chondropathy' checkbox is enabled

And 'Subchondral cysts / geodes' checkbox is enabled
And 'Subchondral edema' checkbox is enabled
And 'Subchondral sclerosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Synovial cyst' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bone marrow edema, circumscribed' checkbox is enabled
And 'Moderate' radio button is enabled
And 'Distinct' radio button is enabled

When I select all parts on Localizer
Then all parts are selected and turn red

When I select 'Chondropathy' checkbox
Then 'Grade I' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade II' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade III' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade IV' radio button is enabled

And 'Size' checkbox is enabled
And 'Chondrocalcinosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Unipolar' radio button is enabled
And 'Bipolar' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Size' checkbox
Then 'Largest diameter' input field is enabled

When I select 'Unipolar' checkbox
Then 'Femur' radio button is enabled
And 'Tibia' radio button is enabled
